gurmukhi: qo so n nwQu AnwQ n mo sir qo so n dwnI n mo so iBKwrI
transliteration: To So N Naadu Anaad N Mo Sari , To So N Daanee N Mo So Bhikhaaree ?
translation: O  True Guru! there is no Master like You. But there is no one as dependent as I am. There is no one as great a donor as You and there is no beggar as needy as me.

gurmukhi: mo so n dIn dieAwlu n qo sir mo so AigAwnu n qo so ibcwrI
transliteration: Mo So N Deen Daiaalu N To Sari , Mo So Agiaanu N To So Bichaaree ?
translation: No one is as miserable as I am but none is as clement as You. No one is as ignorant as I am but there is no one as knowledgeable as You.

gurmukhi: mo so n pqiq n pwvn qo sir mo so ibkwrI n qo so aupkwrI
transliteration: Mo So N Patati N Paavan To Sari , Mo So Bikaaree N To So Oupakaaree ?
translation: There is no one who has fallen so low in his deeds and actions as I am. But there is no one else who can purify anyone as much as you. There is no one as sinful as I am and none who can do good as much as you can.

gurmukhi: myry hY Avgun qU gun swgr jwq rswql Et iqhwrI ]528]
transliteration: Mayray Hai Avagoun Too Goun Saagara , Jaat Rasaatal Aot Tihaaree ?528?
translation: I am full of faults and demerits but You are an ocean of virtues. You are my refuge on my way to hell.  (528)
